1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:01:00,000
(Watch on www.kisskh.xyz Support Admin)

2
00:01:34,900 --> 00:01:37,610
[Bloom Life]

3
00:01:38,560 --> 00:01:42,440
[2007]

4
00:01:40,640 --> 00:01:41,860
The prince and the princess

5
00:01:41,860 --> 00:01:43,990
lived happily ever after.

6
00:01:44,690 --> 00:01:46,530
How about we play princesses?

7
00:01:52,220 --> 00:01:54,020
What's so good about a princess?

8
00:01:54,070 --> 00:01:56,150
She has to walk like that.

9
00:01:56,780 --> 00:01:58,670
Either being tricked by a wicked queen

10
00:01:58,670 --> 00:02:00,230
or chased by an evil dragon.

11
00:02:03,570 --> 00:02:05,700
Always needing someone to rescue her.

12
00:02:05,940 --> 00:02:08,340
Who says a princess always needs rescuing?

13
00:02:08,500 --> 00:02:09,470
Minawar could play

14
00:02:09,470 --> 00:02:10,470
a brave princess.

15
00:02:11,420 --> 00:02:14,650
The kind that's pretty, beautiful,
and courageous.

16
00:02:15,160 --> 00:02:16,490
I want to play an elf,

17
00:02:16,579 --> 00:02:17,920
a magic-wielding elf.

18
00:02:17,930 --> 00:02:21,579
I can make everyone happy
with a wave of my wand,

19
00:02:22,079 --> 00:02:23,210
except the bad guys.

20
00:02:23,470 --> 00:02:24,420
What about you, Arzugul?

21
00:02:24,420 --> 00:02:26,510
I'm definitely going to play the prince.

22
00:02:26,510 --> 00:02:27,930
I'll defeat the evil dragon

23
00:02:27,930 --> 00:02:29,060
and save my kingdom.

24
00:02:30,300 --> 00:02:31,360
Here is your crown!

25
00:02:44,240 --> 00:02:47,710
[Episode 4: Food and weeds grow together]

26
00:02:59,590 --> 00:03:02,930
As the old saying goes,
the distance between your eyebrows

27
00:03:03,020 --> 00:03:08,080
is the distance you'll travel from home.

28
00:03:08,330 --> 00:03:09,610
I've applied Osman grass to your eyebrows

29
00:03:09,610 --> 00:03:12,870
since you were little,

30
00:03:12,870 --> 00:03:16,410
because I hope you'll stay close to home.

31
00:03:17,610 --> 00:03:19,490
It's fine if you don't go to Shanghai.

32
00:03:19,490 --> 00:03:22,600
Stay home and be closer to Grandma.

33
00:03:30,430 --> 00:03:32,320
Is your dad still not eating?

34
00:03:34,020 --> 00:03:35,070
No.

35
00:03:35,440 --> 00:03:36,490
It's different this time.

36
00:03:36,490 --> 00:03:38,430
Before, no matter how big the problem was,

37
00:03:38,430 --> 00:03:42,340
I could go coax him, and it would work.

38
00:03:44,270 --> 00:03:46,870
My dad cares more about his face
than anything.

39
00:03:48,040 --> 00:03:49,770
But this time he's really hurt.

40
00:03:50,400 --> 00:03:52,770
It's not just about face.

41
00:03:52,800 --> 00:03:54,500
He's worried about you.

42
00:03:54,740 --> 00:03:57,050
You need to think it over yourself.

43
00:04:14,140 --> 00:04:15,710
Your in-laws are not easy to deal with.

44
00:04:15,710 --> 00:04:17,470
We're all afraid you'll get bullied.

45
00:04:17,470 --> 00:04:19,410
What else can I do, Arzugul?

46
00:04:19,940 --> 00:04:22,440
Sadiq and I are the ones living together.

47
00:04:23,230 --> 00:04:25,630
If I have to, I'll just keep out of
their way.

48
00:04:29,110 --> 00:04:30,340
Don't worry about me.

49
00:04:30,360 --> 00:04:31,360
Look at yourself.

50
00:04:39,580 --> 00:04:41,159
So beautiful.

51
00:04:52,990 --> 00:04:54,220
I told you.

52
00:04:54,240 --> 00:04:56,100
That Gulhumar is no simple woman.

53
00:04:56,260 --> 00:04:59,210
And her daughter is fierce too.

54
00:05:00,710 --> 00:05:03,960
On the wedding day, she tore down
the bride's red cloth

55
00:05:04,380 --> 00:05:05,500
straight away.

56
00:05:06,720 --> 00:05:08,050
And at the wedding,

57
00:05:08,560 --> 00:05:09,880
Sadiq's family

58
00:05:10,150 --> 00:05:12,880
didn't exchange a single word
with their family.

59
00:05:13,850 --> 00:05:16,850
Uncle Elishir's face was beyond grim.

60
00:05:16,850 --> 00:05:17,640
Is it?

61
00:05:17,640 --> 00:05:18,680
Kid,

62
00:05:18,830 --> 00:05:21,450
watch your mouth and don't talk nonsense.

63
00:05:21,850 --> 00:05:25,410
I think those two families getting married

64
00:05:25,410 --> 00:05:29,880
is like an ant marrying an elephant.

65
00:05:30,010 --> 00:05:32,680
An ant marries an elephant.

66
00:05:33,770 --> 00:05:36,600
A few days later, the elephant dies.

67
00:05:36,630 --> 00:05:39,190
What does the ant do then?

68
00:05:39,210 --> 00:05:39,950
Do you know?

69
00:05:40,130 --> 00:05:41,790
It tries to bury the elephant.

70
00:05:41,920 --> 00:05:44,120
It keeps trying,

71
00:05:44,150 --> 00:05:47,090
spending its whole life doing it.

72
00:05:48,680 --> 00:05:50,030
As far as I know,

73
00:05:50,230 --> 00:05:51,830
here's how it really went...

74
00:05:52,350 --> 00:05:53,050
Go on.

75
00:05:53,520 --> 00:05:54,480
Why did you stop?

76
00:05:55,560 --> 00:05:56,320
Go on.

77
00:05:56,640 --> 00:05:58,560
Tell me what you know.

78
00:06:03,070 --> 00:06:05,420
How could you gossip with them like that?

79
00:06:05,440 --> 00:06:07,040
I was just stating the facts.

80
00:06:07,770 --> 00:06:09,080
Sadiq's family are snobs.

81
00:06:09,080 --> 00:06:09,710
Everyone knows that.

82
00:06:09,710 --> 00:06:11,030
You were not stating the facts.

83
00:06:11,030 --> 00:06:12,490
You were just stirring up trouble.

84
00:06:12,490 --> 00:06:14,550
How is she supposed to live this down?

85
00:06:16,620 --> 00:06:18,250
I saw you two from far away.

86
00:06:18,520 --> 00:06:19,930
Are you two young lovers having a spat?

87
00:06:19,930 --> 00:06:21,310
Who are you calling lovers?

88
00:06:21,310 --> 00:06:22,960
If you can't talk properly,
just don't say anything.

89
00:06:22,960 --> 00:06:24,540
With so many people in your family,

90
00:06:24,540 --> 00:06:26,130
none of you know how to talk properly.

91
00:06:26,130 --> 00:06:27,930
What did my family ever do to you?

92
00:06:27,950 --> 00:06:28,590
Minawar's little sister

93
00:06:28,590 --> 00:06:29,260
is my little sister too, right?

94
00:06:29,260 --> 00:06:31,720
Come here, I'll teach you how to
talk to elders.

95
00:06:31,720 --> 00:06:33,120
Sorry, Brother-in-law.

96
00:06:33,180 --> 00:06:34,440
This kid is a bit rowdy.

97
00:06:34,909 --> 00:06:35,659
I'll take her home.

98
00:06:35,659 --> 00:06:36,260
Shut up.

99
00:06:36,870 --> 00:06:38,200
Little girl, with such a bad temper,

100
00:06:38,200 --> 00:06:39,420
who would dare marry you?

101
00:06:39,420 --> 00:06:41,150
Don't make sarcastic remarks there.

102
00:06:41,150 --> 00:06:41,930
I'll just say what I want.

103
00:06:41,930 --> 00:06:43,060
You think you're great just because
you're rich?

104
00:06:43,060 --> 00:06:44,000
Yes, I'm great.

105
00:06:44,020 --> 00:06:45,080
You're great?

106
00:06:45,100 --> 00:06:45,860
You're great?

107
00:06:45,860 --> 00:06:46,920
What are you doing?

108
00:06:48,130 --> 00:06:49,240
I just smashed it, so what?

109
00:06:49,240 --> 00:06:50,170
I'll pay for it.

110
00:06:50,580 --> 00:06:52,610
Are you out of your mind?

111
00:06:54,020 --> 00:06:54,870
What are you doing?

112
00:06:54,870 --> 00:06:55,730
What happened?

113
00:06:55,880 --> 00:06:56,760
What happened?

114
00:06:56,780 --> 00:06:57,740
Honey, you came at the right time.

115
00:06:57,740 --> 00:06:58,570
It was just a joke.

116
00:06:58,570 --> 00:06:59,590
Was it necessary to smash my car?

117
00:06:59,590 --> 00:07:00,260
You're talking nonsense.

118
00:07:00,260 --> 00:07:01,520
What do you mean by “talking nonsense”?

119
00:07:01,520 --> 00:07:02,820
She has such a bad temper.

120
00:07:02,820 --> 00:07:04,090
You started it on me first.

121
00:07:04,090 --> 00:07:05,470
What do you mean by
“I started on you first”?

122
00:07:05,470 --> 00:07:06,890
Say a little less. Say a little less.

123
00:07:06,890 --> 00:07:07,690
Laili,

124
00:07:07,920 --> 00:07:09,800
when will you ever change
this temper of yours?

125
00:07:09,800 --> 00:07:10,320
Go inside.

126
00:07:10,320 --> 00:07:10,820
Fine, fine.

127
00:07:10,820 --> 00:07:12,080
Honey, don't be angry.

128
00:07:12,130 --> 00:07:13,280
Let's go, hurry up.

129
00:07:13,630 --> 00:07:14,600
Alright, it's nothing.

130
00:07:14,600 --> 00:07:15,350
Laili,

131
00:07:15,650 --> 00:07:17,450
I'll go and have it fixed myself.

132
00:07:18,640 --> 00:07:20,240
What's going on with you two?

133
00:07:20,870 --> 00:07:21,990
One of you made a scene at my wedding,

134
00:07:21,990 --> 00:07:23,660
upsetting the whole family.

135
00:07:24,690 --> 00:07:26,790
And the other, within days,
smashed my husband's car.

136
00:07:26,790 --> 00:07:28,340
Yes, we have nothing better to do.

137
00:07:28,340 --> 00:07:30,090
But weren't we doing it for your own good?

138
00:07:30,090 --> 00:07:33,620
Your mother‑in‑law and the others
really went too far that day.

139
00:07:33,920 --> 00:07:34,520
To be honest,

140
00:07:34,520 --> 00:07:35,320
I don't care at all

141
00:07:35,320 --> 00:07:36,920
what Sadiq's family is like.

142
00:07:38,159 --> 00:07:40,640
As long as he can take me
away from the inn, it's fine.

143
00:07:40,640 --> 00:07:42,900
What did the Camel Bell Inn
ever do to you?

144
00:07:47,610 --> 00:07:49,340
Can you smell that smell?

145
00:07:50,530 --> 00:07:51,420
What smell?

146
00:07:52,810 --> 00:07:54,140
The smell of livestock.

147
00:07:54,290 --> 00:07:57,090
The livestock pen was torn down
over ten years ago.

148
00:07:57,850 --> 00:07:59,850
But I can still smell it.

149
00:08:01,450 --> 00:08:03,710
I feel like it's forever stuck in my nose.

150
00:08:06,760 --> 00:08:08,760
Of course you don't mind that smell,

151
00:08:08,880 --> 00:08:11,310
because this is just a temporary stop
for you.

152
00:08:11,310 --> 00:08:13,000
But I'm not like you, Arzugul.

153
00:08:13,270 --> 00:08:14,690
I was born here.

154
00:08:16,000 --> 00:08:16,910
Sometimes I feel

155
00:08:16,910 --> 00:08:18,860
like I'll never get out of this place
this whole life.

156
00:08:18,860 --> 00:08:20,380
Wasn't I born here too?

157
00:08:20,630 --> 00:08:22,630
Isn't this the place that raised me?

158
00:08:23,670 --> 00:08:24,290
You just don't know

159
00:08:24,290 --> 00:08:25,840
how much I envy you

160
00:08:25,870 --> 00:08:27,640
every day when I see your family
all together.

161
00:08:27,640 --> 00:08:29,330
I wish I could live here
with my mom and dad too.

162
00:08:29,330 --> 00:08:30,640
That's because you've been outside.

163
00:08:30,640 --> 00:08:32,039
Can you understand that?

164
00:08:37,120 --> 00:08:39,380
Those girls I used to learn dance with...

165
00:08:39,830 --> 00:08:41,419
Some married big bosses.

166
00:08:42,200 --> 00:08:44,340
Some found rich boys.

167
00:08:44,540 --> 00:08:46,300
I also want a beautiful house

168
00:08:46,360 --> 00:08:47,620
and my own car.

169
00:08:47,640 --> 00:08:48,980
You can have them.

170
00:08:49,010 --> 00:08:50,460
You can get them by yourself.

171
00:08:50,460 --> 00:08:52,190
Why do you have to rely on others?

172
00:08:52,190 --> 00:08:54,030
You always say “by yourself, by yourself.”

173
00:08:54,030 --> 00:08:55,730
Didn't your house in Shanghai also
run into trouble?

174
00:08:55,730 --> 00:08:56,170
I got the house in Shanghai

175
00:08:56,170 --> 00:08:57,950
also through my own hard work.

176
00:08:57,980 --> 00:08:58,720
So what now?

177
00:08:58,740 --> 00:09:01,070
Did I get it through my own hard work
or not?

178
00:09:02,810 --> 00:09:04,340
Both of you, say a little less.

179
00:09:04,340 --> 00:09:06,340
That's just how the world works.

180
00:09:06,500 --> 00:09:08,040
I will grow old and ugly.

181
00:09:08,200 --> 00:09:09,530
There will always be someone
to replace me.

182
00:09:09,530 --> 00:09:11,640
How long can I keep dancing
in the song and dance troupe?

183
00:09:11,640 --> 00:09:13,530
Stop bringing your big‑city mentality

184
00:09:13,530 --> 00:09:14,530
over here, alright?

185
00:09:14,530 --> 00:09:16,030
What “big‑city mentality” of ours?

186
00:09:16,030 --> 00:09:17,620
Now I have nothing.

187
00:09:17,720 --> 00:09:18,670
I lost my job.

188
00:09:18,690 --> 00:09:19,310
I lost my house.

189
00:09:19,310 --> 00:09:20,040
I have nothing at all.

190
00:09:20,040 --> 00:09:21,840
What “mentality” do I have left?

191
00:09:22,430 --> 00:09:23,670
Say a little less.

192
00:09:23,960 --> 00:09:25,620
Both of you, say a little less.

193
00:09:26,220 --> 00:09:27,430
And you, Laili,

194
00:09:27,860 --> 00:09:29,250
do you think you know me so well?

195
00:09:29,250 --> 00:09:30,740
You don't know me at all.

196
00:09:30,770 --> 00:09:32,560
Just don't make trouble for me,
that's all.

197
00:09:32,560 --> 00:09:34,340
Right. No one knows you.

198
00:09:34,370 --> 00:09:35,970
Only you know yourself best.

199
00:09:57,810 --> 00:09:58,550
Nur,

200
00:09:59,730 --> 00:10:01,110
tell me.

201
00:10:02,270 --> 00:10:04,190
We all grew up here.

202
00:10:04,900 --> 00:10:06,480
Why do they look down on me?

203
00:10:06,900 --> 00:10:09,070
I own a shop in the busiest spot

204
00:10:09,100 --> 00:10:11,030
in the old town.

205
00:10:11,740 --> 00:10:14,200
That was over ten years ago.

206
00:10:14,230 --> 00:10:16,600
It's different now.

207
00:10:16,620 --> 00:10:18,620
How many times have I told you?

208
00:10:19,750 --> 00:10:22,920
Renovate your shop.

209
00:10:23,170 --> 00:10:25,040
But you just won't listen to me.

210
00:10:25,520 --> 00:10:28,420
If you decorate your shop
and make it look nice,

211
00:10:28,510 --> 00:10:30,400
then the money will just

212
00:10:30,400 --> 00:10:32,580
come flowing in.

213
00:10:32,950 --> 00:10:35,040
Do you know how much

214
00:10:35,060 --> 00:10:37,800
that Dragon Spring Homestay costs
per night?

215
00:10:38,630 --> 00:10:40,630
It's just three hundred yuan.

216
00:10:41,630 --> 00:10:42,890
What are you talking about?

217
00:10:42,890 --> 00:10:43,910
Not three hundred.

218
00:10:43,910 --> 00:10:45,380
When there're a lot of tourists
in the old town,

219
00:10:45,380 --> 00:10:47,970
it can make fifteen hundred a night.

220
00:10:48,000 --> 00:10:49,150
Fifteen hundred?

221
00:10:51,400 --> 00:10:52,490
Even an emperor's palace

222
00:10:52,490 --> 00:10:55,220
wouldn't cost fifteen hundred a night,
would it?

223
00:10:55,630 --> 00:10:57,960
Timur, do you agree?

224
00:10:59,990 --> 00:11:01,510
Timur won't say anything.

225
00:11:01,650 --> 00:11:03,870
Timur has very sharp ears,

226
00:11:03,990 --> 00:11:05,740
but he says nothing.

227
00:11:07,060 --> 00:11:09,130
Every wrinkle on Timur's face

228
00:11:09,200 --> 00:11:12,050
hides everyone's secrets.

229
00:11:14,420 --> 00:11:15,220
Ah, by the way,

230
00:11:16,300 --> 00:11:20,350
you used to sing Peking Opera really well.

231
00:11:21,350 --> 00:11:24,830
I haven't sung that song for a long time.

232
00:11:24,860 --> 00:11:27,790
You haven't forgotten it, have you?
Sing a bit for us.

233
00:11:28,060 --> 00:11:30,870
♪ Wearing a red star on my head ♪

234
00:11:30,890 --> 00:11:33,840
♪ Red flags of revolution on both sides ♪

235
00:11:33,870 --> 00:11:36,150
♪ Where the red flag points,
dark clouds scatter ♪

236
00:11:36,170 --> 00:11:39,840
♪ The people of the liberated area overthrow
the landlords and stand up ♪

237
00:11:39,970 --> 00:11:45,420
♪ The people's army ♪

238
00:11:45,560 --> 00:11:50,370
♪ shares weal and woe with the people ♪

239
00:11:50,400 --> 00:11:53,030
♪ They have come here ♪

240
00:11:53,350 --> 00:11:55,880
♪ to wipe out bandits
in the Tiger Mountain ♪

241
00:11:56,010 --> 00:11:58,130
Bravo!

242
00:12:06,240 --> 00:12:07,230
Grandma,

243
00:12:08,460 --> 00:12:10,920
can I sleep with you tonight?

244
00:12:12,150 --> 00:12:14,260
Did you three have a fight?

245
00:12:17,330 --> 00:12:18,950
Are you angry?

246
00:12:22,010 --> 00:12:24,510
Grandma.

247
00:12:24,530 --> 00:12:25,590
My granddaughter.

248
00:12:26,570 --> 00:12:28,190
Do you know why

249
00:12:29,130 --> 00:12:32,900
on the rooftops of our house
and your friend Laili's house,

250
00:12:32,920 --> 00:12:36,770
low walls that even a lamb can jump over

251
00:12:37,080 --> 00:12:39,510
are still standing there?

252
00:12:40,870 --> 00:12:43,540
No matter how close two people are,

253
00:12:43,920 --> 00:12:48,580
they shouldn't cross the line.

254
00:12:50,040 --> 00:12:51,870
I see, Grandma.

255
00:13:00,370 --> 00:13:01,460
Young man,

256
00:13:01,460 --> 00:13:02,470
weren't you going to stay for three days?

257
00:13:02,470 --> 00:13:03,780
Why are you leaving now?

258
00:13:03,780 --> 00:13:05,540
The facilities in your rooms

259
00:13:05,540 --> 00:13:06,900
are too terrible.

260
00:13:07,000 --> 00:13:09,250
The hair dryer trips the breaker
every time we use it.

261
00:13:09,250 --> 00:13:10,090
For the past two days, my girlfriend

262
00:13:10,090 --> 00:13:11,550
had to sleep with wet hair.

263
00:13:11,820 --> 00:13:13,080
What do you say to that?

264
00:13:13,300 --> 00:13:15,140
We just spent over 200 yuan on medicine.

265
00:13:15,140 --> 00:13:16,510
We won't ask you to pay for it.

266
00:13:16,510 --> 00:13:18,040
Just refund us the room fee for the two days
and the deposit

267
00:13:18,040 --> 00:13:19,430
to our original payment account.

268
00:13:19,430 --> 00:13:20,570
Miss,

269
00:13:20,850 --> 00:13:22,350
if you put it that way,

270
00:13:22,370 --> 00:13:24,100
you are making it difficult for me.

271
00:13:24,100 --> 00:13:25,000
Bro,

272
00:13:25,350 --> 00:13:26,550
is this the medicine?

273
00:13:27,830 --> 00:13:28,520
Uncle,

274
00:13:28,550 --> 00:13:29,260
you made a mistake.

275
00:13:29,260 --> 00:13:30,790
You delivered it to my room.

276
00:13:34,700 --> 00:13:36,680
It's 30.75 yuan.

277
00:13:37,090 --> 00:13:38,350
Nowhere near 200 yuan.

278
00:13:39,800 --> 00:13:40,320
Bro,

279
00:13:41,010 --> 00:13:42,110
when you are away from home,

280
00:13:42,110 --> 00:13:44,040
you shouldn't be hard on yourself,

281
00:13:44,260 --> 00:13:46,990
nor should you make things difficult
for others.

282
00:13:48,860 --> 00:13:49,930
Keep the medicine.

283
00:13:49,950 --> 00:13:50,810
How about this?

284
00:13:50,950 --> 00:13:52,400
We will give you a 20% discount.

285
00:13:52,400 --> 00:13:53,640
And we'll return the deposit to you.

286
00:13:53,640 --> 00:13:54,450
Is that okay?

287
00:13:55,250 --> 00:13:56,130
Alright, alright.

288
00:13:56,130 --> 00:13:57,340
Let's leave it at that.

289
00:13:57,340 --> 00:13:58,440
Then refund the money quickly.

290
00:13:58,440 --> 00:13:59,970
Yes, yes. Sorry about that.

291
00:14:00,000 --> 00:14:01,260
Sorry, sorry.

292
00:14:01,280 --> 00:14:02,500
Enjoy your stay!

293
00:14:03,690 --> 00:14:04,430
Young man,

294
00:14:04,840 --> 00:14:06,750
