295
00:14:07,470 --> 00:14:08,440
Well, Uncle,

296
00:14:08,710 --> 00:14:10,640
your water heater

297
00:14:10,670 --> 00:14:11,920
alternates between hot and cold.

298
00:14:11,920 --> 00:14:12,510
And also,

299
00:14:12,510 --> 00:14:13,370
the Wi-Fi

300
00:14:13,390 --> 00:14:14,540
keeps disconnecting.

301
00:14:14,540 --> 00:14:15,120
Well,

302
00:14:15,300 --> 00:14:16,780
I won't check out.

303
00:14:17,130 --> 00:14:18,830
Just give me a 30% discount,

304
00:14:19,410 --> 00:14:20,010
alright?

305
00:14:20,490 --> 00:14:21,090
Stop it, stop it.

306
00:14:21,090 --> 00:14:22,040
Let's have breakfast first.

307
00:14:22,040 --> 00:14:23,010
We Kashgar people

308
00:14:23,010 --> 00:14:24,160
don't talk about sad things

309
00:14:24,160 --> 00:14:25,460
during breakfast.

310
00:14:25,460 --> 00:14:26,750
Come on.

311
00:14:26,750 --> 00:14:27,470
Have breakfast first.

312
00:14:27,470 --> 00:14:28,560
Come here.

313
00:14:29,370 --> 00:14:29,870
Sit down and have breakfast.

314
00:14:29,870 --> 00:14:30,870
Uncle, 20% discount, alright?

315
00:14:30,870 --> 00:14:31,750
No, no, no.

316
00:14:31,750 --> 00:14:33,160
The faucet is broken again!

317
00:14:33,160 --> 00:14:33,630
Take a seat.

318
00:14:33,630 --> 00:14:35,510
I'll go fix the faucet for you.

319
00:14:35,700 --> 00:14:36,900
I'm to fix the faucet.

320
00:14:36,920 --> 00:14:37,580
I'm coming.

321
00:14:39,910 --> 00:14:44,150
Many old craftsmen
can't make this pot well.

322
00:14:45,680 --> 00:14:46,880
It's just because...

323
00:14:49,210 --> 00:14:51,140
Master, does your hand hurt again?

324
00:14:52,460 --> 00:14:53,060
Dad,

325
00:14:54,230 --> 00:14:55,020
let me do it.

326
00:14:55,610 --> 00:14:57,180
I bought you gloves.

327
00:14:57,180 --> 00:14:58,780
Why aren't you wearing them?

328
00:14:58,860 --> 00:15:00,950
You don't listen to the doctor at all.

329
00:15:01,300 --> 00:15:02,900
Those gloves are too big.

330
00:15:03,250 --> 00:15:04,430
I can't feel anything.

331
00:15:04,430 --> 00:15:06,230
Then go ahead and ruin your hand.

332
00:15:06,660 --> 00:15:07,420
Alright, alright.

333
00:15:07,420 --> 00:15:08,820
It doesn't hurt anymore.

334
00:15:08,900 --> 00:15:10,500
Go back to your own business.

335
00:15:11,850 --> 00:15:14,130
What's a girl doing making trouble here?

336
00:15:15,130 --> 00:15:18,130
Look, this pot still isn't good enough.

337
00:15:18,150 --> 00:15:20,430
Hold the clay with your hands

338
00:15:20,460 --> 00:15:23,320
and pull it up slowly like this.

339
00:15:34,660 --> 00:15:35,570
What's wrong?

340
00:15:36,090 --> 00:15:37,990
-Grandma.
-Are you upset, Laili?

341
00:15:39,600 --> 00:15:41,600
No, Grandma.

342
00:15:42,010 --> 00:15:44,010
That's good.

343
00:15:44,460 --> 00:15:46,590
Then don't just play with your phone.

344
00:15:46,880 --> 00:15:49,560
Help Grandma with some chores.

345
00:15:49,590 --> 00:15:50,790
No problem, Grandma.

346
00:16:06,850 --> 00:16:09,400
Grandma, are you sure the radio is
on the rooftop?

347
00:16:09,400 --> 00:16:12,140
I thought I saw it on the courtyard bed
yesterday.

348
00:16:13,370 --> 00:16:16,400
It should be on the rooftop.
Go up and check.

349
00:16:26,440 --> 00:16:28,580
If you don't make up,

350
00:16:29,290 --> 00:16:31,980
none of you are allowed to come out.

351
00:16:32,000 --> 00:16:32,570
Grandma!

352
00:16:33,460 --> 00:16:34,160
Grandma!

353
00:16:34,460 --> 00:16:35,230
Grandma!

354
00:16:35,510 --> 00:16:36,060
Grandma!

355
00:16:36,400 --> 00:16:37,490
We made up.

356
00:16:37,730 --> 00:16:39,710
Grandma, we really made up.

357
00:16:39,820 --> 00:16:41,210
You really did?

358
00:16:41,300 --> 00:16:42,160
Really.

359
00:16:43,230 --> 00:16:44,960
Then hug each other and show me.

360
00:17:02,780 --> 00:17:04,660
