was the Spring Equinox.

422
00:20:21,800 --> 00:20:22,800
Around that time,

423
00:20:23,870 --> 00:20:25,700
the migrating birds

424
00:20:25,700 --> 00:20:27,210
and ducks

425
00:20:27,650 --> 00:20:30,950
all returned to the stream by the meadow.

426
00:20:31,880 --> 00:20:33,740
Even they all settled down there.

427
00:20:41,100 --> 00:20:41,890
Alright.

428
00:20:42,260 --> 00:20:42,820
Let's go.

429
00:20:43,570 --> 00:20:44,210
Let me do it.

430
00:20:44,210 --> 00:20:45,180
I can make it.

431
00:20:45,180 --> 00:20:46,100
The cart is so heavy.

432
00:20:46,100 --> 00:20:47,530
It's really not heavy. I can handle it.

433
00:20:47,530 --> 00:20:48,380
Are you sure?

434
00:20:48,400 --> 00:20:49,190
Yes.

435
00:20:50,870 --> 00:20:52,000
You are so stubborn.

436
00:20:52,160 --> 00:20:53,590
Why are you so stubborn as a mule?

437
00:20:53,590 --> 00:20:55,450
Yeah, I'm just stubborn as a mule.

438
00:20:55,940 --> 00:20:57,140
Don't push yourself.

439
00:21:20,410 --> 00:21:22,610
One, two, three.

440
00:21:38,120 --> 00:21:39,030
Sorry.

441
00:21:39,850 --> 00:21:40,760
Does it hurt?

442
00:21:43,320 --> 00:21:44,290
What?

443
00:21:44,910 --> 00:21:47,040
Are you going to take responsibility?

444
00:21:49,920 --> 00:21:51,550
I was just kidding.

445
00:21:54,610 --> 00:21:56,580
If I can't carry you to the peak of life,

446
00:21:56,580 --> 00:21:58,640
at least when you're going downhill,

447
00:21:58,770 --> 00:22:00,900
there's someone to cushion your fall.

448
00:22:07,070 --> 00:22:07,880
Xia Zi.

449
00:22:10,020 --> 00:22:11,620
I want to give you a job offer.

450
00:22:28,570 --> 00:22:29,810
I want to turn this entire shop

451
00:22:29,810 --> 00:22:30,990
into the most distinctive

452
00:22:30,990 --> 00:22:32,790
new type of homestay in Kashgar.

453
00:22:33,550 --> 00:22:34,630
So I need someone

454
00:22:34,660 --> 00:22:36,280
who understands both aesthetics
and Kashgar

455
00:22:36,280 --> 00:22:38,010
to help me with the renovation.

456
00:22:38,380 --> 00:22:38,880
Also,

457
00:22:39,620 --> 00:22:41,960
I need you to help me convince the family.

458
00:23:03,440 --> 00:23:04,370
You can't sleep？

459
00:23:05,200 --> 00:23:06,400
I can't sleep either.

460
00:23:11,270 --> 00:23:12,180
Before,

461
00:23:12,200 --> 00:23:13,930
I used to work at a big tech firm.

462
00:23:14,160 --> 00:23:15,680
After paying rent each month,

463
00:23:15,680 --> 00:23:17,100
more than half of my salary was gone.

464
00:23:17,100 --> 00:23:19,070
I worked overtime until 9 p.m. every day,

465
00:23:19,070 --> 00:23:20,130
just like you said.

466
00:23:20,410 --> 00:23:23,540
Because after 9 p.m.,
the taxi ride home was reimbursed.

467
00:23:25,610 --> 00:23:27,070
Once I finally got home

468
00:23:27,090 --> 00:23:28,620
and had some time to myself,

469
00:23:28,650 --> 00:23:30,980
I got into the bad habit of
staying up late.

470
00:23:33,770 --> 00:23:35,300
Why are you telling me this?

471
00:23:35,530 --> 00:23:38,460
To say that you're as much of
a corporate slave as I am?

472
00:23:42,910 --> 00:23:44,320
I do have insomnia,

473
00:23:45,290 --> 00:23:46,720
but mine only started

474
00:23:46,740 --> 00:23:48,420
in the last couple of years.

475
00:23:49,340 --> 00:23:50,630
Whenever I can't sleep,

476
00:23:50,630 --> 00:23:52,130
I like listening to music.

477
00:23:53,330 --> 00:23:55,220
Maybe because I grew up here,

478
00:23:56,060 --> 00:23:57,360
I feel like

479
00:23:57,380 --> 00:23:59,320
singing and dancing

480
00:23:59,710 --> 00:24:01,830
are already in my blood.

481
00:24:04,180 --> 00:24:05,710
When I can't sleep at night,

482
00:24:05,810 --> 00:24:06,970
I just sing.

483
00:24:09,310 --> 00:24:11,710
When I can't see anything clearly
at night,

484
00:24:12,070 --> 00:24:13,350
I feel like

485
00:24:13,690 --> 00:24:16,330
the sound of singing can wrap around me
like a circle.

486
00:24:16,330 --> 00:24:17,930
It makes me feel really safe.

487
00:24:25,500 --> 00:24:29,130
♪ The sun goes down, but tomorrow
it will climb again ♪

488
00:24:29,420 --> 00:24:34,340
♪ The sun goes down, but tomorrow
it will climb again ♪

489
