500
00:25:42,510 --> 00:25:43,800
It's a match!

501
00:25:57,620 --> 00:25:58,400
My friend...

502
00:25:58,580 --> 00:25:59,020
Uncle.

503
00:25:59,050 --> 00:26:00,450
You're here just in time.

504
00:26:00,530 --> 00:26:03,730
Take a look at this internet-famous
check‑in spot I made.

505
00:26:04,000 --> 00:26:04,940
How is it?

506
00:26:04,190 --> 00:26:05,770
[I miss you at the Camel Bell Inn
in Kashgar]

507
00:26:06,020 --> 00:26:06,950
This won't work.

508
00:26:07,380 --> 00:26:09,240
The truth is, running a homestay nowadays

509
00:26:09,240 --> 00:26:10,990
can't rely just on these things.

510
00:26:10,990 --> 00:26:12,200
You need a complete set of

511
00:26:12,200 --> 00:26:14,000
operational logic and methods.

512
00:26:14,790 --> 00:26:15,710
You mean

513
00:26:15,710 --> 00:26:16,770
I should let someone else

514
00:26:16,770 --> 00:26:18,300
manage my place, is that it?

515
00:26:18,340 --> 00:26:20,040
As long as you cooperate with me,

516
00:26:20,040 --> 00:26:20,780
I promise

517
00:26:20,810 --> 00:26:22,940
to give you a completely renewed shop.

518
00:26:23,090 --> 00:26:23,820
How about it?

519
00:26:27,510 --> 00:26:28,400
No, no, no.

520
00:26:28,970 --> 00:26:29,950
No way.

521
00:26:30,680 --> 00:26:31,400
Uncle,

522
00:26:31,740 --> 00:26:32,920
please think about it.

523
00:26:32,920 --> 00:26:33,270
Alright,

524
00:26:33,270 --> 00:26:35,210
I'll think it over later.

525
00:26:40,120 --> 00:26:41,080
Hello.

526
00:26:43,950 --> 00:26:45,080
Wang has been found.

527
00:26:46,240 --> 00:26:46,900
Where?

528
00:26:52,650 --> 00:26:54,250
Hey, friend!

529
00:26:55,320 --> 00:26:56,910
Alimu is so unreliable.

530
00:26:57,420 --> 00:26:59,480
The car he found is even older than me.

531
00:26:59,490 --> 00:27:00,580
See?

532
00:27:00,740 --> 00:27:02,140
It broke down, didn't it?

533
00:27:02,310 --> 00:27:03,360
Wang's last transaction address

534
00:27:03,360 --> 00:27:04,750
provided by the police station

535
00:27:04,750 --> 00:27:06,280
is in Tuogelunxia Village.

536
00:27:06,290 --> 00:27:07,660
If we can flag down a ride now,

537
00:27:07,660 --> 00:27:09,400
we should be able to get there
before evening.

538
00:27:09,400 --> 00:27:10,920
Hey, mister!

539
00:27:11,370 --> 00:27:13,170
Could you give us a ride?

540
00:27:13,190 --> 00:27:13,700
Sure.

541
00:27:13,700 --> 00:27:14,280
Thank you.

542
00:27:14,280 --> 00:27:14,940
Thank you.

543
00:27:29,350 --> 00:27:31,040
Let me tell you.

544
00:27:31,060 --> 00:27:32,180
About that friend tracing app,

545
00:27:32,180 --> 00:27:33,460
I saw my colleague download it,

546
00:27:33,460 --> 00:27:34,550
so I just followed suit.

547
00:27:34,550 --> 00:27:36,750
Then I got too busy and never got back on.

548
00:27:36,760 --> 00:27:38,290
Don't read too much into it.

549
00:27:38,530 --> 00:27:39,590
We matched, right?

550
00:27:39,660 --> 00:27:41,920
That means you swiped right and chose me.

551
00:27:42,020 --> 00:27:44,060
So, does my look

552
00:27:44,080 --> 00:27:45,640
fit your type?

553
00:27:45,930 --> 00:27:47,930
How can you be so shameless?

554
00:27:47,960 --> 00:27:49,960
My finger just slipped at that time.

555
00:27:50,510 --> 00:27:52,810
I was just asking casually.

556
00:28:00,460 --> 00:28:01,940
Once we cross this little hill,

557
00:28:01,940 --> 00:28:03,870
we'll be able to enter the village.

558
00:28:03,970 --> 00:28:05,270
My car can't go in,

559
00:28:05,270 --> 00:28:06,870
so I'll have to drop you here.

560
00:28:06,900 --> 00:28:07,420
Okay.

561
00:28:07,420 --> 00:28:08,290
Thank you, bro.

562
00:28:08,380 --> 00:28:09,200
You're welcome.

563
00:28:09,200 --> 00:28:11,220
Guests are gifts from heaven.

564
00:28:11,730 --> 00:28:13,590
If we're fated, we'll meet again.

565
00:28:17,730 --> 00:28:19,390
Snowy mountains, here I come!

566
00:28:19,510 --> 00:28:20,700
Stop running!

567
00:28:22,840 --> 00:28:24,200
Stop running.

568
00:28:24,470 --> 00:28:26,400
This is the Pamirs.

569
00:28:26,400 --> 00:28:28,660
It's easy to get altitude sickness here.

570
00:28:31,970 --> 00:28:32,720
I can't go on.

571
00:28:33,280 --> 00:28:35,010
I'm a little oxygen‑deprived.

572
00:28:35,510 --> 00:28:37,470
Sorrow comes with too much joy.

573
00:28:38,130 --> 00:28:39,530
Can you keep going or not?

574
00:28:40,660 --> 00:28:41,590
What's the rush?

575
00:28:42,570 --> 00:28:44,170
Let me rest for a while first.

576
00:28:44,460 --> 00:28:46,940
Go rest. I'm not in a hurry anyway.

577
00:28:47,110 --> 00:28:48,570
Wang doesn't owe me money.

578
00:29:00,100 --> 00:29:03,030
You don't have to get up right away
when you fall down.

579
00:29:03,670 --> 00:29:05,070
Just lie down for a while.

580
00:29:06,360 --> 00:29:07,660
Look at the blue sky.

581
00:29:08,360 --> 00:29:09,530
Look at the clouds.

582
00:29:10,620 --> 00:29:12,150
Look at the birds in the sky.

583
00:29:14,770 --> 00:29:16,550
You have so many philosophies.

584
00:29:16,860 --> 00:29:18,400
Just give me a break.

585
00:29:19,510 --> 00:29:20,510
I'll listen to you

586
00:29:20,720 --> 00:29:22,200
and just lie flat, okay?

587
00:29:24,700 --> 00:29:26,600
It's not me who should give you a break.

588
00:29:26,600 --> 00:29:28,800
It's about you giving yourself a break.

589
00:30:32,090 --> 00:30:33,920
Did I just fall asleep?

590
00:30:38,190 --> 00:30:39,450
You dozed off for a bit.

591
00:30:47,230 --> 00:30:49,030
This place is really beautiful.

592
00:30:49,620 --> 00:30:52,150
We have to admit, Wang knows
how to pick a spot.

593
00:30:54,070 --> 00:30:55,990
If he hadn't cheated me out of my money,

594
00:30:55,990 --> 00:30:58,190
I'd really want to have a drink with him.

595
00:30:59,590 --> 00:31:05,090
♪ My beautiful Kuyinaziguli ♪

596
00:31:04,070 --> 00:31:05,790
Two packs of cigarettes,
two bottles of beer...

597
00:31:05,120 --> 00:31:11,760
♪ Your peerless beauty outshines
the mountain flowers ♪

598
00:31:05,790 --> 00:31:08,680
Two bottles of water,
and a pack of compressed biscuits.

599
00:31:08,680 --> 00:31:08,900
Oh!

600
00:31:09,290 --> 00:31:10,440
And a thick hat.

601
00:31:11,230 --> 00:31:12,750
You are his friends?

602
00:31:12,270 --> 00:31:17,570
♪ She's so stunning ♪

603
00:31:13,670 --> 00:31:16,380
Can you pay the rest of his bill?

604
00:31:16,550 --> 00:31:16,880
Okay.

605
00:31:17,530 --> 00:31:18,700
Okay, I'll pay.

606
00:31:17,600 --> 00:31:25,320
♪ I deeply fell in love with her ♪

607
00:31:20,460 --> 00:31:22,180
He still owes you money too.

608
00:31:22,490 --> 00:31:23,860
He might be in trouble.

609
00:31:25,340 --> 00:31:30,090
♪ She's so stunning ♪

610
00:31:26,420 --> 00:31:28,010
You're here to collect a debt, aren't you?

611
00:31:28,010 --> 00:31:29,340
I don't think you'll get it.

612
00:31:29,340 --> 00:31:31,810
He doesn't have 100 yuan to his name.

613
00:31:30,120 --> 00:31:36,810
♪ I deeply fell in love with her ♪

614
00:31:32,140 --> 00:31:34,200
How do you know he is hiding
from creditors?

615
00:31:34,200 --> 00:31:35,570
When a stranger shows up in the village,

616
00:31:35,570 --> 00:31:36,550
either the're a tourist,

617
00:31:36,550 --> 00:31:38,400
or they're visiting relatives or friends.

618
00:31:36,840 --> 00:31:42,100
♪ Now I'm alone at
a high mountain pasture ♪

619
00:31:38,400 --> 00:31:40,000
He doesn't look like either.

620
00:31:40,010 --> 00:31:41,210
I need to close up now.

621
00:31:41,250 --> 00:31:43,100
I'm in a hurry to get to a wedding.

622
00:31:42,130 --> 00:31:45,000
♪ My deep affection day and night
is so strong ♪

623
00:31:43,360 --> 00:31:44,890
It's okay. You can close up.

624
00:31:45,150 --> 00:31:47,380
♪ Would you stay a little longer
here beside me? ♪

625
00:31:45,470 --> 00:31:47,870
Why don't you two come with me
to see the fun?

626
00:31:58,860 --> 00:32:00,660
Right ahead is our wedding site.

627
00:32:00,900 --> 00:32:02,200
Our weddings are very lively.

628
00:32:02,200 --> 00:32:03,380
This is my first time attending

629
00:32:03,380 --> 00:32:04,550
a Tajik wedding.

630
00:32:04,550 --> 00:32:05,550
My first time too.

631
00:32:08,900 --> 00:32:10,160
Isn't that the driver?

632
00:32:10,750 --> 00:32:11,440
Uncle.

633
00:32:11,440 --> 00:32:13,310
Come, sit down.

634
00:32:13,750 --> 00:32:15,360
What a small world!

635
00:32:15,770 --> 00:32:17,660
Is this your family's wedding?

636
00:32:17,660 --> 00:32:19,790
Yes, it's my brother's son's wedding.

637
00:32:20,270 --> 00:32:21,710
Look at the dance they are doing.

638
00:32:21,710 --> 00:32:22,910
It's the eagle dance.

639
00:32:23,120 --> 00:32:25,660
We are the eagles on the Pamirs.

640
00:32:26,070 --> 00:32:28,470
We've guarded this place for generations.

641
00:32:52,310 --> 00:32:54,230
Come and sprinkle flour

642
00:32:54,230 --> 00:32:56,200
to bless the bride and groom!

643
00:33:01,470 --> 00:33:02,750
Congratulations!

644
00:33:07,170 --> 00:33:09,100
Let's go back to Kashgar tomorrow.

645
00:33:09,310 --> 00:33:10,960
You are not looking for Wang anymore?

646
00:33:10,960 --> 00:33:11,900
No.

647
00:33:12,140 --> 00:33:14,420
Maybe Wang really is
in some kind of trouble.

648
00:33:14,420 --> 00:33:15,200
Besides,

649
00:33:15,750 --> 00:33:17,140
such an adventure, such beautiful scenery,

650
00:33:17,140 --> 00:33:18,400
aren't they valuable?

651
00:33:19,570 --> 00:33:21,160
We didn't find the person we want,

652
00:33:21,160 --> 00:33:22,960
but it's totally worth the trip.

653
00:33:24,630 --> 00:33:26,830
I thought you were obsessed with money.

654
00:33:27,620 --> 00:33:28,510
I do love money,

655
00:33:29,030 --> 00:33:30,290
but not just money.

656
00:33:30,900 --> 00:33:32,630
I think such a good house

657
00:33:32,820 --> 00:33:34,360
shouldn't go to waste.

658
00:33:35,140 --> 00:33:35,840
What I want

659
00:33:35,840 --> 00:33:37,170
is a win-win situation.

660
00:33:39,710 --> 00:33:41,360
If you put it that way,

661
00:33:42,310 --> 00:33:44,490
I'll try to convince them for you.

662
00:33:44,990 --> 00:33:47,680
I don't want my family's place
to go out of business either.

663
00:33:47,680 --> 00:33:49,010
I accept your job offer.

664
00:33:49,440 --> 00:33:50,360
Okay, it's a deal then.

665
00:33:50,360 --> 00:33:51,160
It's a deal.

666
00:33:54,290 --> 00:33:55,380
A promise made

667
00:33:55,510 --> 00:33:56,470
can't be taken back.

668
00:33:56,470 --> 00:33:57,340
I'll do my best.

669
00:33:57,640 --> 00:33:58,700
I'll do my best too.

670
00:34:15,030 --> 00:34:15,889
Zhou Hengzhi.

671
00:36:25,050 --> 00:36:28,410
Sorry to make you share the communal bed
with us.

672
00:36:28,670 --> 00:36:31,010
It gets cold here at night.

673
00:36:31,420 --> 00:36:34,570
Sleeping close keeps you warm.

674
00:36:36,840 --> 00:36:38,010
Auntie, thank you. Sorry to trouble you.

675
00:36:38,010 --> 00:36:38,940
You are welcome.

676
00:36:39,030 --> 00:36:39,630
Thank you.

677
00:36:43,850 --> 00:36:44,610
There's only one quilt?

678
00:36:44,610 --> 00:36:45,420
Ah, yes.

679
00:36:45,690 --> 00:36:47,090
No, please give us two.

680
00:36:47,090 --> 00:36:48,490
Ah, okay.

681
00:36:49,840 --> 00:36:51,240
Auntie, let me do it.

682
00:36:51,460 --> 00:36:52,660
It's okay. I'll do it.

683
00:36:53,340 --> 00:36:53,670
Okay.

684
00:36:54,280 --> 00:36:55,630
Sorry for the trouble, Auntie.

685
00:36:55,630 --> 00:36:56,450
It's nothing.

686
00:37:01,900 --> 00:37:02,500
Thank you.

687
00:37:04,550 --> 00:37:05,260
It's done.

688
00:37:05,260 --> 00:37:05,960
Ah, okay.

689
00:37:06,470 --> 00:37:07,470
Ah, tired after a whole day.

690
00:37:07,470 --> 00:37:08,730
Finally time to sleep.

691
00:37:15,910 --> 00:37:17,370
Ah, well...

692
00:37:19,690 --> 00:37:22,050
I'm suddenly not sleepy.

693
00:37:22,070 --> 00:37:23,070
I won't sleep yet.

694
00:37:23,940 --> 00:37:25,140
You just sleep first.

695
00:37:25,670 --> 00:37:27,170
I'll keep a watch for you.

696
00:37:32,440 --> 00:37:33,350
You sleep.

697
00:37:33,470 --> 00:37:34,510
It's okay.

698
00:37:34,510 --> 00:37:35,550
I'm not sleepy.

699
00:37:37,610 --> 00:37:40,800
I'll just look at the

700
00:37:41,130 --> 00:37:42,990
starry sky outside. It's pretty.

701
00:38:35,360 --> 00:38:38,450
[Laili]

702
00:38:41,460 --> 00:38:44,410
I heard from grandma that you went to
Taxkorgan together.

703
00:38:44,410 --> 00:38:46,560
I sent her birthday wishes right on time,

704
00:38:46,560 --> 00:38:47,550
but she ignored me.

705
00:38:47,550 --> 00:38:48,610
Xia Zi's birthday?

706
00:38:48,840 --> 00:38:50,490
Yes, it's today.

707
00:39:01,670 --> 00:39:02,550
Xia Zi,

708
00:39:02,920 --> 00:39:04,050
happy birthday!

709
00:39:07,030 --> 00:39:07,800
What?

710
00:39:09,820 --> 00:39:11,220
I can't hear you clearly.

711
00:39:19,130 --> 00:39:20,380
Happy birthday.

712
00:39:25,270 --> 00:39:25,900
Thank you.

713
00:39:27,240 --> 00:39:27,960
Xia Zi,

714
00:39:29,990 --> 00:39:31,590
now that we're at this point,

715
00:39:33,130 --> 00:39:34,790
the only thing that's certain

716
00:39:35,030 --> 00:39:36,840
is that nothing is certain.

717
00:39:38,430 --> 00:39:41,290
Once you figure it out,
you won't be scared anymore.

718
00:39:42,420 --> 00:39:44,060
We've lost a lot now.

719
00:39:44,630 --> 00:39:45,760
We've been deceived

720
00:39:45,820 --> 00:39:46,710
and bullied.

721
00:39:46,730 --> 00:39:49,260
We feel like failures, get angry
and feel sad.

722
00:39:50,510 --> 00:39:53,150
As long as we're not dead,
let's live well.

723
00:39:55,110 --> 00:39:57,040
Eat a good meal when you're hungry.

724
00:39:57,280 --> 00:39:58,760
Take a nap if you're tired.

725
00:39:59,890 --> 00:40:01,280
Use these little things

726
00:40:01,530 --> 00:40:03,390
to raise yourself all over again.

727
00:41:30,440 --> 00:41:31,630
Hello.

728
00:41:31,760 --> 00:41:32,990
Have you left yet?

729
00:41:34,550 --> 00:41:35,680
It's the shop owner.

730
00:41:36,240 --> 00:41:36,950
What's up?

731
00:41:38,070 --> 00:41:39,200
We haven't left yet.

732
00:41:39,210 --> 00:41:41,460
I've found a car to take you.

733
00:41:41,490 --> 00:41:42,630
Found a car?

734
00:41:51,090 --> 00:41:53,470
Sis, what's planted here?

735
00:41:53,810 --> 00:41:54,880
This side is wheat,

736
00:41:55,150 --> 00:41:56,880
and that side is sea buckthorn.

737
00:41:57,880 --> 00:42:00,060
Shouldn't you pull these weeds?

738
00:42:00,670 --> 00:42:03,670
If you ask me, people elsewhere
are just too diligent.

739
00:42:03,720 --> 00:42:06,340
They rip out all the weeds

740
00:42:06,430 --> 00:42:07,960
that aren't useful to them.

741
00:42:08,060 --> 00:42:09,930
They exterminate all the insects.

742
00:42:09,930 --> 00:42:11,590
Except for the crops people eat,

743
00:42:11,590 --> 00:42:14,050
nothing else are allowed to grow
on the land.

744
00:42:14,260 --> 00:42:15,900
Busy every day,

745
00:42:16,110 --> 00:42:17,200
they never think about a bird

746
00:42:17,200 --> 00:42:19,030
flying overhead.

747
00:42:19,170 --> 00:42:20,560
Where will it land?

748
00:42:20,830 --> 00:42:22,630
Where are its food and water?

749
00:42:23,190 --> 00:42:24,940
But in the fields of Kashgar,

750
00:42:25,040 --> 00:42:27,370
a blade of grass can grow old safely

751
00:42:27,660 --> 00:42:29,780
without worrying about being removed.

752
00:42:29,780 --> 00:42:31,740
Human food and donkey weeds

753
00:42:31,740 --> 00:42:33,610
grow in the same field.

754
00:42:35,010 --> 00:42:38,570
Birds build nests in the trees
above the fields

755
00:42:38,600 --> 00:42:40,930
and catch bugs to eat when they're hungry.

756
00:42:41,010 --> 00:42:42,970
Sometimes they even eat wheat grains.

757
00:42:42,970 --> 00:42:45,100
And people pretend not to notice them.

758
00:42:45,460 --> 00:42:46,790
You talk so eloquently,

759
00:42:47,240 --> 00:42:48,120
and yet you still end up

760
00:42:48,120 --> 00:42:50,250
tired and stressed yourself?

761
00:42:51,050 --> 00:42:52,500
You are relaxed now,

762
00:42:52,530 --> 00:42:54,250
even cheerful when someone owes you money.

763
00:42:54,250 --> 00:42:55,040
You...

764
00:42:57,860 --> 00:42:59,060
You're right anyway.

765
00:42:59,280 --> 00:43:01,020
Just let yourself take a comfortable
little nap.
